News about Red tide: Concentrations Reduced in Pinellas, Manatee, and Sarasota
The latest report from the Florida Fish and Wildlife Commission shows a general decline in red tide concentrations for parts of the Tampa Bay area.
According to the FWC, collegiate flowering conditions in the areas of Pinellas, Manatee, Sarasota, Charlotte, and Collier are reported cities - representing reduced concentrations.
In full bloom, the Red tide extends about 130 miles along the coastline from northern Pinellas to southern Lee cities.
Kolle can be found about 10 miles off the coast of Hillsborough city, but at less locations compared to last week.
Red tide was also observed in Pasco City.
Medium concentrations in or near the coast of Pinellas City have been reported in the past week, low to high concentrations off the coast of Hillsborough City, background to high concentrations in Manatee City, background to high concentrations in or near the coast of Sarasota City, background to medium concentrations in Charlotte City, background to high concentrations in or near the coast of Lee City, and low concentrations in Collier City.
